            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Constat me <persName key="#Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#people/1554">Andreas</persName> gr(aci)a D(e)i <rs key="#Deacons"
                            >diacon(us)</rs> et <rs key="#Monks">monachus</rs> adq(ue) <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abb(as)</rs> regul(e) <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >mon(asterii)</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1487">S(an)c(t)i Apole(na)ri q(ui) voc(atur)
                            Novo</orgName> accepisse(m) et accepit a vob(is) <persName><name
                                ref="Apollinaris">Apolenaris</name></persName> filio q(uon)d(am)
                                <persName><name ref="Iohannes">Ioh(anni)s</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">pensione</rs> p(ro) <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >tres uncias int(e)g(ras)</rs> q(ui) e(st) posita in <rs key="#Fundi"
                            >fundu(m)</rs> q(ui) voc(a)t(ur) <geogName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money" ref="#estates/2421"
                                ><placeName key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money"
                                >Colopedio</placeName></geogName> cu(m) om(n)ib(us) sibi
                        p(er)tinentibus, <rs key="#Fines">territorio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#estates/2422"><placeName
                                key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#places/3515"
                            >Liviense</placeName></geogName>, <rs key="#Plebs">plebe</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/1488">S(an)c(t)e
                            Reparate</orgName>, quas p(er) <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"
                            >enfiteus</rs> tenere viso estis ad iure s(uprascrip)ti mo[n(asterii)
                        n(ost)r]i, et p(er) unaquaq(ue) ind(i)c(ione) <rs key="#Rent_in_kind"
                            >d(e)n(a)ri q(ui)nq(ue) tantu(m)</rs>. Unde p(ro) munimine v(est)ri
                        fecit vob(is) hoc deaccep(to) in m(en)se m(a)r(cio), ind(i)c(ione) nona,
                            <placeName ref="#places/594">Ravena</placeName>. Andreas diacus et abba
                        mon(asterii) S(an)c(t)i Apolena(ris) in oc ed[iac]et s(ub)s(cripsi). </ab>
